264
00:16:17.844 --> 00:16:19.844
[♪♪♪]

265
00:16:30.089 --> 00:16:33.240
Jesus Christ.

266
00:17:00.069 --> 00:17:01.685
[PANTING]

267
00:17:36.021 --> 00:17:38.500
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Renard Parish Sheriff's Department.</i>

268
00:17:38.524 --> 00:17:39.801
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

269
00:17:39.825 --> 00:17:41.419
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

270
00:17:41.443 --> 00:17:43.355
BUD: Sheriff's
Department. <i>Anyone there?</i>

271
00:17:43.379 --> 00:17:44.873
BUD: Anyone in there?

272
00:17:44.897 --> 00:17:47.198
<i>This is the Sheriff's
Department. Can I help you?</i>

273
00:17:49.435 --> 00:17:51.247
<i>Hello?</i>

274
00:17:51.271 --> 00:17:52.481
[SIZZLING]

275
00:17:52.505 --> 00:17:54.004
[MARYANN HUMMING]

276
00:18:19.415 --> 00:18:21.231
[CONTINUES HUMMING]

277
00:18:44.124 --> 00:18:45.990
[ERIC GROANING]

278
00:18:48.761 --> 00:18:51.039
NEWLIN: You see?

279
00:18:51.063 --> 00:18:52.741
Just as our lord. our savior.

280
00:18:52.765 --> 00:18:55.010
was betrayed for
30 pieces of silver.

281
00:18:55.034 --> 00:18:56.579
a few ounces of silver

282
00:18:56.603 --> 00:18:58.981
can betray a child
of Satan to the world!

283
00:18:59.005 --> 00:19:00.649
That doesn't make any sense.

284
00:19:00.673 --> 00:19:02.518
How can you
people listen to him?

285
00:19:02.542 --> 00:19:04.687
I...

286
00:19:04.711 --> 00:19:06.872
I offer myself

287
00:19:06.896 --> 00:19:10.626
in exchange for
Godric's freedom.

288
00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:13.445
And the girl's as well.

289
00:19:13.469 --> 00:19:18.033
That's noble. but she's
just as culpable as you are.

290
00:19:18.057 --> 00:19:20.669
She's a traitor to her race.

291
00:19:20.693 --> 00:19:22.937
The human race.

292
00:19:22.961 --> 00:19:25.445
She hardly deserves mercy.

293
00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.061
Maybe we should tie her to you.

294
00:19:29.085 --> 00:19:31.229
so you can meet
the sun together.

295
00:19:31.253 --> 00:19:34.400
Bet this marshmallow
would roast up nicely.

296
00:19:34.424 --> 00:19:36.251
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

297
00:19:36.275 --> 00:19:39.226
Sookie!

298
00:19:40.430 --> 00:19:43.258
One more step.
vampire. and the girl dies.

299
00:19:43.282 --> 00:19:46.529
If you shoot her.
everyone here will die.

300
00:19:46.553 --> 00:19:48.914
Let her go now.

301
00:19:48.938 --> 00:19:50.749
Honestly. what
do they see in you?

302
00:19:50.773 --> 00:19:53.202
Soldiers. some silver
chains for our friend.

303
00:19:53.226 --> 00:19:55.637
Don't. He's done nothing
to you. Sookie. I will be fine.

304
00:19:55.661 --> 00:19:57.506
JASON: Newlin! [GUNSHOT]

305
00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:59.412
Ah! Ah! [CROWD GASPS]

306
00:20:00.950 --> 00:20:02.683
Let her go. fuckwad!

307
00:20:04.404 --> 00:20:05.748
[GUNSHOT] [CROWD MURMURING]

308
00:20:05.772 --> 00:20:08.601
Ah! Ow!

309
00:20:08.625 --> 00:20:10.435
[GRUNTING]

310
00:20:10.459 --> 00:20:11.842
Son of a bitch!

311
00:20:13.129 --> 00:20:14.907
Sookie.

312
00:20:14.931 --> 00:20:17.443
[GROANING]

313
00:20:17.467 --> 00:20:19.027
SOOKIE: Let's go.

314
00:20:21.638 --> 00:20:22.836
[GRUNTING]

315
00:20:24.057 --> 00:20:26.402
Eric. do not kill him.
JASON: Kill him.

316
00:20:26.426 --> 00:20:28.704
Kill the motherfucker!

317
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:30.706
NEWLIN: Go ahead.

318
00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:33.709
Murder us. Murder us before God.

319
00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:35.366
We are willing to die.

320
00:20:37.070 --> 00:20:40.216
[LOUD RUMBLING]

321
00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:42.506
[GLASS SHATTERS]

322
00:20:43.859 --> 00:20:45.287
Steve Newlin.

323
00:20:45.311 --> 00:20:46.472
Huh?

324
00:20:46.496 --> 00:20:49.113
STAN: You have
pushed us too far.

325
00:20:50.516 --> 00:20:52.577
You expect us to
sit on our thumbs

326
00:20:52.601 --> 00:20:55.481
while you round up your
men to come lynch us?

327
00:20:55.505 --> 00:20:58.288
We'll kill you first.

328
00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:04.106
Same way we did your
father. Oh. God. no.

329
00:21:04.130 --> 00:21:05.908
Murderer!

330
00:21:05.932 --> 00:21:07.243
Ah!

331
00:21:07.267 --> 00:21:10.901
Destroy them. All of them.

332
00:21:11.938 --> 00:21:12.998
[GROWLING]

333
00:21:13.022 --> 00:21:15.367
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

334
00:21:15.391 --> 00:21:17.508
Bill. Eric. stop them!
We have to go now!

335
00:21:19.846 --> 00:21:21.429
GODRIC: Enough.

336
00:21:23.483 --> 00:21:25.483
[♪♪♪]

337
00:21:27.019 --> 00:21:28.686
You came for me. I assume.

338
00:21:29.939 --> 00:21:32.751
Underling?

339
00:21:32.775 --> 00:21:34.520
Yeah. sheriff.

340
00:21:34.544 --> 00:21:37.211
These people have not harmed me.

341
00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:41.894
You see? We can coexist.

342
00:21:41.918 --> 00:21:43.701
Mr. Newlin...

343
00:21:46.005 --> 00:21:47.816
I do not wish to
create bloodshed

344
00:21:47.840 --> 00:21:49.807
where none is called for.

345
00:21:51.260 --> 00:21:54.239
Help me set an example.

346
00:21:54.263 --> 00:21:58.777
If we leave you in peace.
will you do the same?

347
00:21:58.801 --> 00:22:03.737
I will not negotiate
with subhumans.

348
00:22:05.007 --> 00:22:06.551
Kill me. WOMAN: No!

349
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:08.637
NEWLIN: Do it.

350
00:22:08.661 --> 00:22:10.806
Jesus will protect me.

351
00:22:10.830 --> 00:22:13.992
I'm actually older
than your Jesus.

352
00:22:14.016 --> 00:22:17.846
I wish I could have
known him. but I missed it.

353
00:22:17.870 --> 00:22:20.471
[GASPS]

354
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:25.570
Good people. who
of you is willing to die

355
00:22:25.594 --> 00:22:28.579
for this man's madness?

356
00:22:30.433 --> 00:22:32.828
GODRIC: That's what I thought.

357
00:22:32.852 --> 00:22:35.086
Stand down. everyone.

358
00:22:36.889 --> 00:22:41.553
People. go home. It's over now.

359
00:22:41.577 --> 00:22:43.589
Oh. thank God. Bill.

360
00:22:43.613 --> 00:22:45.696
It's all right. You're safe now.

361
00:22:46.833 --> 00:22:49.011
You're safe.

362
00:22:49.035 --> 00:22:52.503
NEWLIN: Please. don't leave me.

363
00:22:54.907 --> 00:22:56.818
[GROANS]

364
00:22:56.842 --> 00:22:59.153
GODRIC: I daresay
my faith in humankind

365
00:22:59.177 --> 00:23:01.628
is stronger than yours.

366
00:23:04.917 --> 00:23:06.417
Come.

367
00:23:10.106 --> 00:23:14.036
Sir. after what these
humans have done to you?

368
00:23:14.060 --> 00:23:15.526
I said. come.

369
00:23:20.817 --> 00:23:22.560
Are you sure you're okay?

370
00:23:22.584 --> 00:23:24.963
She's fine.

371
00:23:24.987 --> 00:23:26.431
Go with your maker.

372
00:23:26.455 --> 00:23:30.207
S-Sookie. Sookie. come here.

373
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:35.940
Oh. I'm so sorry. Will
you please forgive me?

374
00:23:35.964 --> 00:23:38.660
What were you doing with those
people? You out of your mind?

375
00:23:38.684 --> 00:23:41.118
Yeah. I was. Just...

376
00:23:42.538 --> 00:23:44.900
That son of a bitch. it's
like he sucked out my brain

377
00:23:44.924 --> 00:23:46.902
and planted all his
own babies in there.

378
00:23:46.926 --> 00:23:48.987
NEWLIN: You know nothing.

379
00:23:49.011 --> 00:23:52.357
On the final day of reckoning.

380
00:23:52.381 --> 00:23:57.318
we'll see who goes to
heaven and who goes to hell.

381
00:23:58.554 --> 00:24:01.567
I reckon I've already
been to heaven.

382
00:24:01.591 --> 00:24:03.907
It was inside your wife.

383
00:24:05.695 --> 00:24:08.273
Oh! Ow.

384
00:24:08.297 --> 00:24:09.758
Jason. come on.

385
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.092
What about that?

386
00:24:11.116 --> 00:24:13.962
Come on. Take your ring.

387
00:24:13.986 --> 00:24:17.198
JASON: Honesty.
my ass. shithead.

388
00:24:17.222 --> 00:24:19.956
White-suit motherfucker.

389
00:24:21.427 --> 00:24:24.678
Go home. preacher boy.

390
00:24:31.453 --> 00:24:34.066
BUD: <i>Come on. Sam.
We can't tell you that.</i>

391
00:24:34.090 --> 00:24:36.201
That's why it's called
an anonymous tip.

392
00:24:36.225 --> 00:24:38.002
We can't tell you
who phoned it in.

393
00:24:38.026 --> 00:24:41.506
They wanted you to find me.

394
00:24:41.530 --> 00:24:45.032
Why would I keep a body
in my own refrigerator?

395
00:24:46.602 --> 00:24:49.298
Was it a woman's voice? Sam.

396
00:24:49.322 --> 00:24:51.332
There's a rumor you
were having a relationship

397
00:24:51.356 --> 00:24:55.137
with the deceased.
Is that true? Yeah.

398
00:24:55.161 --> 00:24:56.922
Well. you don't seem
too beat up about it.

399
00:24:56.946 --> 00:24:59.324
Well. we...

400
00:24:59.348 --> 00:25:01.927
I guess we kind of broke
up. Were you angry?

401
00:25:01.951 --> 00:25:03.479
Bound to be some hurt feelings.

402
00:25:03.503 --> 00:25:06.615
Listen. y'all have to trust me.

403
00:25:06.639 --> 00:25:11.153
This is bigger and crazier
than you can even imagine.

404
00:25:11.177 --> 00:25:14.289
I'll say. This is the
second time in two weeks

405
00:25:14.313 --> 00:25:16.591
a woman's found in your
bar with her heart missing.

406
00:25:16.615 --> 00:25:19.544
And the third time a waitress
of yours has ended up dead.

407
00:25:19.568 --> 00:25:21.046
Oh. come on. That
was Rene Lenier.

408
00:25:21.070 --> 00:25:23.949
You can't use that against me.

409
00:25:23.973 --> 00:25:27.218
Come on. Bud. Kenya.
Listen to yourselves.

410
00:25:27.242 --> 00:25:29.804
You know me. I'm not sure we do.

411
00:25:29.828 --> 00:25:32.958
You got no birth records.
no Social Security number.

412
00:25:32.982 --> 00:25:35.582
We can't even find where
you went to high school.

413
00:25:36.952 --> 00:25:38.514
It's hard to explain.

414
00:25:38.538 --> 00:25:42.017
Save it. son. Nothing about
your past ever checks out.

415
00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:44.720
Why don't you just tell
us what happened tonight?

416
00:25:44.744 --> 00:25:46.888
[DOOR OPENS]

417
00:25:46.912 --> 00:25:48.190
What the...?

418
00:25:48.214 --> 00:25:50.025
Whoa. Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hold up.

419
00:25:50.049 --> 00:25:51.943
Bud. you don't think
it's Sam. do you?

420
00:25:51.967 --> 00:25:53.807
Let me get him. Hold on. Kenya.

421
00:25:54.971 --> 00:25:56.581
You're on suspension.

422
00:25:56.605 --> 00:25:59.985
How'd you hear about
this? Still got my radio.

423
00:26:00.009 --> 00:26:02.587
I'm not here as a cop.
okay? I'm a witness.

424
00:26:02.611 --> 00:26:04.673
You got the wrong guy. What?

425
00:26:04.697 --> 00:26:06.858
Sam's not the one
you want. He's a victim.

426
00:26:06.882 --> 00:26:09.294
I saw him nearly
get killed last night.

427
00:26:09.318 --> 00:26:11.163
By who? The bull.

428
00:26:11.187 --> 00:26:13.765
The what? Oh. Andy.

429
00:26:13.789 --> 00:26:15.751
He thinks he saw
some kind of bull.

430
00:26:15.775 --> 00:26:18.887
With claws. A bull. In a dress.

431
00:26:18.911 --> 00:26:20.055
With claws.

432
00:26:20.079 --> 00:26:21.823
Okay. Andy. you're
babbling again.

433
00:26:21.847 --> 00:26:23.559
I can shut him up. And your vic.

434
00:26:23.583 --> 00:26:26.228
That vic you got in there. she
was part of this whole group

435
00:26:26.252 --> 00:26:28.180
of crazy people that
was trying to get him.

436
00:26:28.204 --> 00:26:32.551
I tried to fight 'em
off. but... War wound.

437
00:26:32.575 --> 00:26:36.504
I'm corroborating here.
Sam. Tell them. Help me.

438
00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:38.888
If I told you that's what
happened. would you believe me?

439
00:26:44.687 --> 00:26:48.133
Oh. shit.

440
00:26:48.157 --> 00:26:49.751
[SIGHS]

441
00:26:49.775 --> 00:26:52.420
But you're not the only one.

442
00:26:52.444 --> 00:26:55.857
I blacked out last night.
Arlene blacked out.

443
00:26:55.881 --> 00:26:58.126
Maybe there's some kind
of gas leak or something.

444
00:26:58.150 --> 00:27:00.128
But what about Andy Bellefleur?

445
00:27:00.152 --> 00:27:02.029
H-He said he saw all of us.

446
00:27:02.053 --> 00:27:06.368
Andy's the only one
we know is out his mind.

447
00:27:06.392 --> 00:27:09.036
Tara...

448
00:27:09.060 --> 00:27:12.907
I got this sick feeling I
did something real bad.

449
00:27:12.931 --> 00:27:15.277
MARYANN: Knock. knock.

450
00:27:15.301 --> 00:27:17.379
Hope I'm not interrupting.

451
00:27:17.403 --> 00:27:19.081
No. we're just trying
to piece together

452
00:27:19.105 --> 00:27:21.833
everything we been
doing past couple days.

453
00:27:21.857 --> 00:27:24.135
Mm.

454
00:27:24.159 --> 00:27:27.777
Sounds like somebody's been
enjoying himself a bit too much.

455
00:27:30.182 --> 00:27:32.911
Tell you what. Why don't
we ease up on the partying

456
00:27:32.935 --> 00:27:34.613
for a little while? Hm?

457
00:27:34.637 --> 00:27:36.503
Take it easy.

458
00:27:39.475 --> 00:27:42.125
Hey. Snack's ready.

459
00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:50.478
[CHUCKLES]

460
00:27:50.502 --> 00:27:52.781
Hope you're hungry.

461
00:27:52.805 --> 00:27:54.349
TARA: Oh. my God.

462
00:27:54.373 --> 00:27:56.184
That looks amazing. What is it?

463
00:27:56.208 --> 00:27:58.186
Hunter's soufflé.

464
00:27:58.210 --> 00:28:00.322
I didn't know hunters
made soufflés.

465
00:28:00.346 --> 00:28:02.612
Most don't. Dig in.

466
00:28:12.624 --> 00:28:14.958
[♪♪♪]

467
00:28:40.352 --> 00:28:42.230
Goddamn.

468
00:28:42.254 --> 00:28:45.067
What is in there? Is that
the rabbit you caught?

469
00:28:45.091 --> 00:28:46.689
Among other things.

470
00:28:47.893 --> 00:28:49.237
Mm.

471
00:28:49.261 --> 00:28:51.895
You have got to try this.

472
00:28:57.869 --> 00:28:59.581
Mm.

473
00:28:59.605 --> 00:29:03.356
Oh. my God. Ha-ha.

474
00:29:15.504 --> 00:29:18.449
[MARYANN CHUCKLES]

475
00:29:18.473 --> 00:29:21.118
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

476
00:29:21.142 --> 00:29:23.104
Mm.

477
00:29:23.128 --> 00:29:24.428
Mm.

478
00:29:27.683 --> 00:29:29.683
[CHATTER]

479
00:29:34.607 --> 00:29:36.885
WOMAN: Thank you. sir.

480
00:29:36.909 --> 00:29:38.787
STAN: Welcome home. sheriff.

481
00:29:38.811 --> 00:29:41.628
We are all very relieved.

482
00:29:47.686 --> 00:29:49.531
Well. I just want
to say I'm real sorry

483
00:29:49.555 --> 00:29:52.189
for what the Fellowship
put you through.

484
00:29:55.744 --> 00:29:58.690
GODRIC: You helped save
many lives today. Mr. Stackhouse.

485
00:29:58.714 --> 00:30:02.310
Please know you have friends
in this area whenever you visit.

486
00:30:02.334 --> 00:30:04.745
Thanks. man. but.
uh. I don't know if I'll be

487
00:30:04.769 --> 00:30:07.086
wanting to come
back anytime soon.

488
00:30:11.326 --> 00:30:13.260
[SOFTLY] God.

489
00:30:18.533 --> 00:30:20.845
Hail the conquering hero.

490
00:30:20.869 --> 00:30:23.514
Oh. no. I'm no hero.

491
00:30:23.538 --> 00:30:25.634
No. you are in this town.

492
00:30:25.658 --> 00:30:27.435
But in my area we know you well

493
00:30:27.459 --> 00:30:30.255
as a buyer and user
of vampire blood.

494
00:30:30.279 --> 00:30:32.156
And that's a very grave offense.

495
00:30:32.180 --> 00:30:34.726
Yeah. listen. I-I
don't do that no more.

496
00:30:34.750 --> 00:30:38.885
All things considered.
however. we'll call it even.

497
00:30:41.207 --> 00:30:43.390
But you won't be doing it again.

498
00:30:44.860 --> 00:30:47.322
Yeah. No. No.

499
00:30:47.346 --> 00:30:49.157
No. Got it.

500
00:30:49.181 --> 00:30:51.164
Good boy. Run along.

501
00:30:58.323 --> 00:31:00.501
WOMAN: It's the
best we could do.

502
00:31:00.525 --> 00:31:03.593
Thanks. this is great.

503
00:31:05.064 --> 00:31:07.876
You've avoided being
alone with me all night.

504
00:31:07.900 --> 00:31:09.778
Nonsense. With
all the commotion.

505
00:31:09.802 --> 00:31:10.879
there's hardly been time.

506
00:31:10.903 --> 00:31:13.714
Bill. I was in that
basement for two days.

507
00:31:13.738 --> 00:31:14.815
You don't even want to know

508
00:31:14.839 --> 00:31:16.718
what almost happened
to me down there.

509
00:31:16.742 --> 00:31:18.587
Where were you?

510
00:31:18.611 --> 00:31:19.888
Sookie. it's...

511
00:31:19.912 --> 00:31:23.091
"It's complicated"
is not an answer.

512
00:31:23.115 --> 00:31:24.592
Every time I've needed you.

513
00:31:24.616 --> 00:31:28.462
you've always come
running. even in broad daylight.

514
00:31:28.486 --> 00:31:30.570
What kept you?

515
00:31:32.440 --> 00:31:33.818
I was held.

516
00:31:33.842 --> 00:31:37.722
Held? Like kidnapped?

517
00:31:37.746 --> 00:31:40.257
By who?

518
00:31:40.281 --> 00:31:42.176
By Eric?

519
00:31:42.200 --> 00:31:44.045
ERIC: Mmm.

520
00:31:44.069 --> 00:31:47.966
Heard my name. I hope
you were speaking well of me.

521
00:31:47.990 --> 00:31:50.919
Why should I? You
let me walk into a trap.

522
00:31:50.943 --> 00:31:53.505
I regret that. If I had
known it was a possibility...

523
00:31:53.529 --> 00:31:57.759
You did know. But because it
was Godric. you'd risk anything.

524
00:31:57.783 --> 00:31:59.861
